Text.SourceString: Oh, you’re the new farmer.//I was worried there for a bit about a potential competitor.//<portrait=happy>Nothing to worry about, it seems.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you’re the new farmer.//I was worried there for a bit about a potential competitor.//<portrait=happy>Nothing to worry about, it seems.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Walter</> and I own the vineyard, you see. Our clients are mostly abroad.//<portrait=normal>Shall I send over a bottle?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Walter</> and I own the vineyard, you see. Our clients are mostly abroad.//<portrait=normal>Shall I send over a bottle?

Text.SourceString: Ugh… Every time I walk past that recycling center, I get a headache.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh… Every time I walk past that recycling center, I get a headache.

Text.SourceString: What are people putting in there? I thought we agreed to only put in clean, recyclable items.//<portrait=annoyed>Obviously, some people don’t know what clean means.
Text.LocalizedString: What are people putting in there? I thought we agreed to only put in clean, recyclable items.//<portrait=annoyed>Obviously, some people don’t know what clean means.

Text.SourceString: The recycling center is such an eyesore. We want to recycle, but there’s no place to do it.
Text.LocalizedString: The recycling center is such an eyesore. We want to recycle, but there’s no place to do it.

Text.SourceString: How much longer are we going to let this pile up?
Text.LocalizedString: How much longer are we going to let this pile up?

Text.SourceString: By the way, <NpcName>Ben</> sells seeds too.//If <NpcName>Sam</> is ever closed, give <NpcName>Ben</> a try.
Text.LocalizedString: By the way, <NpcName>Ben</> sells seeds too.//If <NpcName>Sam</> is ever closed, give <NpcName>Ben</> a try.

Text.SourceString: In fact, I buy a lot of things from him.//To help out his business a little, you see.
Text.LocalizedString: In fact, I buy a lot of things from him.//To help out his business a little, you see.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Ben</> is tricky. His shop is often closed on weekdays.//If you want to give him a visit, I’d recommend going on the weekend.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Ben</> is tricky. His shop is often closed on weekdays.//If you want to give him a visit, I’d recommend going on the weekend.

Text.SourceString: I can't be sure about <NpcName>Ben's</> business hours.//Best take the initiative and find out for yourself.
Text.LocalizedString: I can't be sure about <NpcName>Ben's</> business hours.//Best take the initiative and find out for yourself.

Text.SourceString: You see, we are quite particular about our seeds at the vineyard. Quality consistency is essential.//<portrait=annoyed>I presume you grasp the importance of that, yes?
Text.LocalizedString: You see, we are quite particular about our seeds at the vineyard. Quality consistency is essential.//<portrait=annoyed>I presume you grasp the importance of that, yes?

Text.SourceString: In the world of winemaking, the grape is king. Quality wine is impossible without quality grapes.
Text.LocalizedString: In the world of winemaking, the grape is king. Quality wine is impossible without quality grapes.

Text.SourceString: The same goes for our sake.//The key to good produce is good seeds.
Text.LocalizedString: The same goes for our sake.//The key to good produce is good seeds.

Text.SourceString: We maintain a strict business model—our products are exclusively available to licensed liquor establishments.
Text.LocalizedString: We maintain a strict business model—our products are exclusively available to licensed liquor establishments.

Text.SourceString: These days, I prefer homemade meals as much as possible.//<portrait=happy>I consider it my way of making amends for the carelessness of my youth. Such a laugh.
Text.LocalizedString: These days, I prefer homemade meals as much as possible.//<portrait=happy>I consider it my way of making amends for the carelessness of my youth. Such a laugh.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Dinda’s</> a dear friend of mine. She’s always so sweet.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Dinda’s</> a dear friend of mine. She’s always so sweet.

Text.SourceString: She makes the best homemade meals.//<Italic>Sometimes</> even better than my own.//<portrait=normal>It might be because she grows her own herbs. Yes…that must be it.
Text.LocalizedString: She makes the best homemade meals.//<Italic>Sometimes</> even better than my own.//<portrait=normal>It might be because she grows her own herbs. Yes…that must be it.

Text.SourceString: Never neglect breakfast, <PlayerName>$player</>. It's fundamental!//Skipping it will only leave you famished and prone to overeating.
Text.LocalizedString: Never neglect breakfast, <PlayerName>$player</>. It's fundamental!//Skipping it will only leave you famished and prone to overeating.

Text.SourceString: Farming, to me, is therapeutic. Nurturing plants from seedlings and witnessing their growth is a serene experience.
Text.LocalizedString: Farming, to me, is therapeutic. Nurturing plants from seedlings and witnessing their growth is a serene experience.

Text.SourceString: Doesn't farming give you a sense of tranquility, too?
Text.LocalizedString: Doesn't farming give you a sense of tranquility, too?

Text.SourceString: We should meet up and talk about farming sometime, since we both seem to be working in the same field now.//<portrait=happy>Oh! That’s a pun!
Text.LocalizedString: We should meet up and talk about farming sometime, since we both seem to be working in the same field now.//<portrait=happy>Oh! That’s a pun!

Text.SourceString: But let's keep our little farming chats under wraps. We wouldn't want to incite any petty jealousy.
Text.LocalizedString: But let's keep our little farming chats under wraps. We wouldn't want to incite any petty jealousy.

Text.SourceString: Doing dishes is a chore, and it takes forever. To be perfectly honest, I’d rather cook all day.//<portrait=normal>I’m more gifted in that area.
Text.LocalizedString: Doing dishes is a chore, and it takes forever. To be perfectly honest, I’d rather cook all day.//<portrait=normal>I’m more gifted in that area.

Text.SourceString: Being a farmer in this little town is so much fun. A lot more fun than playing the wife in the big city.
Text.LocalizedString: Being a farmer in this little town is so much fun. A lot more fun than playing the wife in the big city.

Text.SourceString: I always look forward to the town’s charming little holidays too.
Text.LocalizedString: I always look forward to the town’s charming little holidays too.

Text.SourceString: How’s your Summer going, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Mine’s been good, though I can’t seem to find my pearl earrings this morning.//<portrait=annoyed>The ones <NpcName>Walter’s</> mother gave me. Now, if you think <NpcName>Walter</> is eccentric, wait till you meet his mother.
Text.LocalizedString: How’s your Summer going, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Mine’s been good, though I can’t seem to find my pearl earrings this morning.//<portrait=annoyed>The ones <NpcName>Walter’s</> mother gave me. Now, if you think <NpcName>Walter</> is eccentric, wait till you meet his mother.

Text.SourceString: I need to find the earrings before our next dinner with her.//I can’t risk getting on her bad side again.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to find the earrings before our next dinner with her.//I can’t risk getting on her bad side again.

Text.SourceString: We make sure to have enough grapes to make wine year-round.
Text.LocalizedString: We make sure to have enough grapes to make wine year-round.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Taco</>’s a very independent pup. He likes to explore.//Sometimes I worry about him getting lost.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</>’s a very independent pup. He likes to explore.//Sometimes I worry about him getting lost.

Text.SourceString: But he always comes home.//He’s a smart one.
Text.LocalizedString: But he always comes home.//He’s a smart one.

Text.SourceString: It was my idea to move here. I told <NpcName>Walter</> to stop chasing wealth and start enjoying it instead.//<portrait=happy>>After all, we're rather well off, wouldn't you say?//<portrait=normal>Please excuse my bluntness sometimes. I hope you don’t mind.
Text.LocalizedString: It was my idea to move here. I told <NpcName>Walter</> to stop chasing wealth and start enjoying it instead.//<portrait=happy>>After all, we're rather well off, wouldn't you say?//<portrait=normal>Please excuse my bluntness sometimes. I hope you don’t mind.

Text.SourceString: About a year after we settled here, we were graced with our <NpcName>Luke</>.//My precious little <NpcName>Luke</>.
Text.LocalizedString: About a year after we settled here, we were graced with our <NpcName>Luke</>.//My precious little <NpcName>Luke</>.

Text.SourceString: The good thing about this place is that it still feels sleepy on the weekend.//Oh no, no, no, don’t get me wrong. It’s a good thing.//<portrait=happy>We <Italic>want</> sleepy.
Text.LocalizedString: The good thing about this place is that it still feels sleepy on the weekend.//Oh no, no, no, don’t get me wrong. It’s a good thing.//<portrait=happy>We <Italic>want</> sleepy.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Taco</>’s a very happy puppy. We’re so glad he came to live with us.//<portrait=normal>He’s precious. I’ve grown attached to him very quickly.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Taco</>’s a very happy puppy. We’re so glad he came to live with us.//<portrait=normal>He’s precious. I’ve grown attached to him very quickly.

Text.SourceString: He has <Italic>so</> many friends around town, you know. He’s popular.//I think his best friend is our neighbor <NpcName>Archie</>.//Ah, and that curly dog. The small barky one.
Text.LocalizedString: He has <Italic>so</> many friends around town, you know. He’s popular.//I think his best friend is our neighbor <NpcName>Archie</>.//Ah, and that curly dog. The small barky one.

Text.SourceString: Have you settled in yet? Take your time, dear. I didn’t feel like this was home for years.//I felt comfortable right away, sure. But home? That’s always been hard for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you settled in yet? Take your time, dear. I didn’t feel like this was home for years.//I felt comfortable right away, sure. But home? That’s always been hard for me.

Text.SourceString: It must be a shock to your system, moving here from a big city.
Text.LocalizedString: It must be a shock to your system, moving here from a big city.

Text.SourceString: I usually don’t like getting my hands dirty, but I just feel better when I’m working in the soil.
Text.LocalizedString: I usually don’t like getting my hands dirty, but I just feel better when I’m working in the soil.

Text.SourceString: It’s like I’m giving back to Mother Earth. It gives me a purpose in life, yeah.//<portrait=happy>Intense, I know.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s like I’m giving back to Mother Earth. It gives me a purpose in life, yeah.//<portrait=happy>Intense, I know.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Luke</> handles all the vineyard business except for the farming side.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Luke</> handles all the vineyard business except for the farming side.

Text.SourceString: He even does quality control to keep our standards high.//<portrait=normal>I’m very proud of him. He’ll do very well when he takes over.
Text.LocalizedString: He even does quality control to keep our standards high.//<portrait=normal>I’m very proud of him. He’ll do very well when he takes over.

Text.SourceString: My favorite style of painting has to be impressionism.//<portrait=happy>The short, strong brushstrokes really capture the essence of the subject without getting bogged down in the details.
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite style of painting has to be impressionism.//<portrait=happy>The short, strong brushstrokes really capture the essence of the subject without getting bogged down in the details.

Text.SourceString: It shows that something doesn’t have to be logical to be beautiful.//<portrait=normal>It really gets me, you know.
Text.LocalizedString: It shows that something doesn’t have to be logical to be beautiful.//<portrait=normal>It really gets me, you know.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Walter</> can be stubborn sometimes, especially when it comes to big decisions.//<portrait=concerned>But he isn’t half as pushy as some people. You know?
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Walter</> can be stubborn sometimes, especially when it comes to big decisions.//<portrait=concerned>But he isn’t half as pushy as some people. You know?

Text.SourceString: Okay, maybe he is pushy, but just not with me.//As long as he isn’t that way with me, I’m all right.
Text.LocalizedString: Okay, maybe he is pushy, but just not with me.//As long as he isn’t that way with me, I’m all right.

Text.SourceString: We don’t necessarily have to grow grapes all year-round.//In Winter, we focus on other aspects of the vineyard.
Text.LocalizedString: We don’t necessarily have to grow grapes all year-round.//In Winter, we focus on other aspects of the vineyard.

Text.SourceString: But it’s nice to know we have an extra supply.//<portrait=annoyed>Don’t you grow a surplus on your farm? Tsk, tsk, tsk. I hope you do, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//It’s for your own good.
Text.LocalizedString: But it’s nice to know we have an extra supply.//<portrait=annoyed>Don’t you grow a surplus on your farm? Tsk, tsk, tsk. I hope you do, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//It’s for your own good.

Text.SourceString: If wild vegetables pique your interest, you're in for a treat.//Our land is quite generous in that regard.
Text.LocalizedString: If wild vegetables pique your interest, you're in for a treat.//Our land is quite generous in that regard.

Text.SourceString: You're more than welcome to forage here often.//We don't mind.
Text.LocalizedString: You're more than welcome to forage here often.//We don't mind.

Text.SourceString: I heard about Pufferfish moving in. I’d rather not discuss it right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I heard about Pufferfish moving in. I’d rather not discuss it right now.

Text.SourceString: It’s a bit upsetting, isn’t it? We came here to this beautiful island, hoping to get away from big corporations.//Then a part of the past followed us.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a bit upsetting, isn’t it? We came here to this beautiful island, hoping to get away from big corporations.//Then a part of the past followed us.

Text.SourceString: I hope you enjoyed the New Year’s gathering, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you enjoyed the New Year’s gathering, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Up to your standards, I hope?
Text.LocalizedString: Up to your standards, I hope?

Text.SourceString: It was such a blast last week at the lake. It’s a great way to keep the community close.
Text.LocalizedString: It was such a blast last week at the lake. It’s a great way to keep the community close.

Text.SourceString: I brought some bok choy, and nobody touched it. What is it with vegetables, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Is it just because they’re green?
Text.LocalizedString: I brought some bok choy, and nobody touched it. What is it with vegetables, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Is it just because they’re green?

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I do miss modeling. The glam, the people…//But I don’t miss all of it. Some of it was rough.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I do miss modeling. The glam, the people…//But I don’t miss all of it. Some of it was rough.

Text.SourceString: It was tiring. Moonlighting at clubs every night to make ends meet until I got my big break…//That was the plan, anyway.
Text.LocalizedString: It was tiring. Moonlighting at clubs every night to make ends meet until I got my big break…//That was the plan, anyway.

Text.SourceString: Obviously, I never got my big break.//<portrait=normal>But that’s a story for another time.
Text.LocalizedString: Obviously, I never got my big break.//<portrait=normal>But that’s a story for another time.

Text.SourceString: You can grow grapes in Fall. Are you planting some this year?//I don’t know if you’ll be able to plant them now. If I were you, I’d wait until Fall arrives and start then.
Text.LocalizedString: You can grow grapes in Fall. Are you planting some this year?//I don’t know if you’ll be able to plant them now. If I were you, I’d wait until Fall arrives and start then.

Text.SourceString: Looking for tips? Oh, I’d love to give you some.//<portrait=normal>You have to ferment rice in a keg for several days to make sake.
Text.LocalizedString: Looking for tips? Oh, I’d love to give you some.//<portrait=normal>You have to ferment rice in a keg for several days to make sake.

Text.SourceString: Farming is easier if you have automatic sprinklers.//But not everybody needs them.
Text.LocalizedString: Farming is easier if you have automatic sprinklers.//But not everybody needs them.

Text.SourceString: If you only have a few rows of crops, you could probably do without them.
Text.LocalizedString: If you only have a few rows of crops, you could probably do without them.

Text.SourceString: There was a period when <NpcName>Luke</> dyed his hair bright blue. Then he grew it out really long.//<portrait=normal>No, no – without the blue dye.
Text.LocalizedString: There was a period when <NpcName>Luke</> dyed his hair bright blue. Then he grew it out really long.//<portrait=normal>No, no – without the blue dye.

Text.SourceString: Actually, it was more like he grew it out really tall.//<portrait=normal>I wish he’d kept that style. He looked very nice that way.
Text.LocalizedString: Actually, it was more like he grew it out really tall.//<portrait=normal>I wish he’d kept that style. He looked very nice that way.

Text.SourceString: Oh no! It’s Winter already. I need to start getting ready for the annual feast.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no! It’s Winter already. I need to start getting ready for the annual feast.

Text.SourceString: Oh my! I’m glad your toes are all covered up and warm.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my! I’m glad your toes are all covered up and warm.

Text.SourceString: We certainly don’t want them to freeze. Great call!
Text.LocalizedString: We certainly don’t want them to freeze. Great call!

Text.SourceString: Oh, it’s hard to work in this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, it’s hard to work in this weather.

Text.SourceString: I better hurry.
Text.LocalizedString: I better hurry.

Text.SourceString: It’s been raining like this all day. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: It’s been raining like this all day. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: I have to be somewhere. Please excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to be somewhere. Please excuse me.

Text.SourceString: Oh, it’s hard to work in this weather.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, it’s hard to work in this weather.

Text.SourceString: I better hurry.
Text.LocalizedString: I better hurry.

Text.SourceString: It’s been raining like this all day. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: It’s been raining like this all day. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: Oh no. You seem flushed, <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re coming down with a cold! Get some rest!
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no. You seem flushed, <PlayerName>$player</>. You’re coming down with a cold! Get some rest!

Text.SourceString: I have to be somewhere. Please excuse me.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to be somewhere. Please excuse me.

Text.SourceString: Once, I went to this beautiful ski resort in a small town down south.//It looked exactly like this when it snowed.
Text.LocalizedString: Once, I went to this beautiful ski resort in a small town down south.//It looked exactly like this when it snowed.

Text.SourceString: Ah dear! I’ll have to ask <NpcName>Luke</> to shovel the snow tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah dear! I’ll have to ask <NpcName>Luke</> to shovel the snow tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: Winter nights can be really lonely, don’t you think?//I think it’s the sense that the year is ending.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter nights can be really lonely, don’t you think?//I think it’s the sense that the year is ending.

Text.SourceString: It makes you think about all the things you haven’t done.
Text.LocalizedString: It makes you think about all the things you haven’t done.

Text.SourceString: Have you eaten, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Would you like some tea? Or coffee?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you eaten, <PlayerName>$player</>?//Would you like some tea? Or coffee?

Text.SourceString: Are you looking for <NpcName>Taco</>?//He should be around here somewhere.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you looking for <NpcName>Taco</>?//He should be around here somewhere.

Text.SourceString: I make my own bread when I can. <NpcName>Eva’s</> is a little too chewy. It’s not the best for soup.
Text.LocalizedString: I make my own bread when I can. <NpcName>Eva’s</> is a little too chewy. It’s not the best for soup.

Text.SourceString: In Summer, I usually grill whatever fruit or vegetables I can find and just drizzle honey on them.
Text.LocalizedString: In Summer, I usually grill whatever fruit or vegetables I can find and just drizzle honey on them.

Text.SourceString: We have cold drinks in the fridge. Feel free!
Text.LocalizedString: We have cold drinks in the fridge. Feel free!

Text.SourceString: Sorry about the mess! I haven’t straightened up.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry about the mess! I haven’t straightened up.

Text.SourceString: I wasn’t expecting company.
Text.LocalizedString: I wasn’t expecting company.

Text.SourceString: The soil here is ideal for grapes.//And there’s the hills and just the right amount of sunlight.
Text.LocalizedString: The soil here is ideal for grapes.//And there’s the hills and just the right amount of sunlight.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Luke</> used to run around the vineyard when he was little, and he’d eat grapes until his stomach hurt. Ah, ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Luke</> used to run around the vineyard when he was little, and he’d eat grapes until his stomach hurt. Ah, ha ha.

Text.SourceString: That boy has no self-control.
Text.LocalizedString: That boy has no self-control.

Text.SourceString: There aren’t a lot of wild fruits here, for some reason.
Text.LocalizedString: There aren’t a lot of wild fruits here, for some reason.

Text.SourceString: I always loved gardening. But who’d have thought I’d actually enjoy making a living out of it?
Text.LocalizedString: I always loved gardening. But who’d have thought I’d actually enjoy making a living out of it?

Text.SourceString: I was a little bored at home. There wasn’t much to do.
Text.LocalizedString: I was a little bored at home. There wasn’t much to do.

Text.SourceString: Not everyone can do woodwork. You need certain skills, plus, it’s labor intensive.
Text.LocalizedString: Not everyone can do woodwork. You need certain skills, plus, it’s labor intensive.

Text.SourceString: I’m just bringing over some baked goods…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just bringing over some baked goods…

Text.SourceString: And gossiping a little about the townies, right, <NpcName>Dinda</>? Ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: And gossiping a little about the townies, right, <NpcName>Dinda</>? Ha ha.

Text.SourceString: Live music in the evening is always a good idea.
Text.LocalizedString: Live music in the evening is always a good idea.

Text.SourceString: Umm, I felt like dancing tonight, so I just skipped cooking dinner and came here instead.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm, I felt like dancing tonight, so I just skipped cooking dinner and came here instead.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Bree</> is snapping her fingers slightly off-beat.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Bree</> is snapping her fingers slightly off-beat.]

Text.SourceString: Yummy. I wonder what <NpcName>Frank</> puts in this.
Text.LocalizedString: Yummy. I wonder what <NpcName>Frank</> puts in this.

Text.SourceString: I need to pick up some flour. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: I need to pick up some flour. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: I wonder what <NpcName>Eva</> puts in this insanely delicious cake.//I’m determined to find out her secret!
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what <NpcName>Eva</> puts in this insanely delicious cake.//I’m determined to find out her secret!

Text.SourceString: Ah, fresh flowers sound good, don’t they, <PlayerName>$player</>? They really cheer the place up.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, fresh flowers sound good, don’t they, <PlayerName>$player</>? They really cheer the place up.

Text.SourceString: It’s important to take care of yourself. It’s not selfish.//<portrait=happy>On the contrary, it can really improve your performance, and it’s good for your mood.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s important to take care of yourself. It’s not selfish.//<portrait=happy>On the contrary, it can really improve your performance, and it’s good for your mood.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I just want to chop my hair off, but I probably won’t.//Ha ha ha! I don’t think it would suit me.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I just want to chop my hair off, but I probably won’t.//Ha ha ha! I don’t think it would suit me.

Text.SourceString: I guess I know where <NpcName>Luke</> gets his indecisiveness.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess I know where <NpcName>Luke</> gets his indecisiveness.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Walter</> would go wild if I came home with pink hair or something.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Walter</> would go wild if I came home with pink hair or something.

Text.SourceString: My Monday has been wonderful. How’s yours?
Text.LocalizedString: My Monday has been wonderful. How’s yours?

Text.SourceString: The New Year’s Festival is coming up.//I have to take care of the seating, catering, and minigames.
Text.LocalizedString: The New Year’s Festival is coming up.//I have to take care of the seating, catering, and minigames.

Text.SourceString: Oh, it’s incredibly stressful!//I need my old assistant back.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, it’s incredibly stressful!//I need my old assistant back.

Text.SourceString: I can’t comment on our caterer for the New Year’s Festival event. It’s going to be a surprise!
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t comment on our caterer for the New Year’s Festival event. It’s going to be a surprise!

Text.SourceString: I’m keeping it a secret so everybody’s surprised.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m keeping it a secret so everybody’s surprised.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to try a new recipe today.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to try a new recipe today.

Text.SourceString: Oh dang! I ran out of basil. Let’s see if I can just cook this without it.//<portrait=concerned>Would it taste funny, you think, if I changed the basil to ginger? I’ve got plenty of ginger.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh dang! I ran out of basil. Let’s see if I can just cook this without it.//<portrait=concerned>Would it taste funny, you think, if I changed the basil to ginger? I’ve got plenty of ginger.

Text.SourceString: I wish <NpcName>Luke</> would worry less. He overthinks things sometimes.//<portrait=concerned>I keep telling him to stop worrying. It’s no use.//It’ll give you unnecessary wrinkles.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish <NpcName>Luke</> would worry less. He overthinks things sometimes.//<portrait=concerned>I keep telling him to stop worrying. It’s no use.//It’ll give you unnecessary wrinkles.

Text.SourceString: What are you doing here, <PlayerName>$player</>? Picking up a new wall clock?
Text.LocalizedString: What are you doing here, <PlayerName>$player</>? Picking up a new wall clock?

Text.SourceString: Aren’t they great? Maybe I’ll get one myself for the house.
Text.LocalizedString: Aren’t they great? Maybe I’ll get one myself for the house.

Text.SourceString: Live music in the evening is always a good idea. *dances in her seat*
Text.LocalizedString: Live music in the evening is always a good idea. *dances in her seat*

Text.SourceString: People back in the city used to stare at me when I was out with <NpcName>Walter</>.//This was way before we had <NpcName>Luke</>.
Text.LocalizedString: People back in the city used to stare at me when I was out with <NpcName>Walter</>.//This was way before we had <NpcName>Luke</>.

Text.SourceString: People don’t do that here. They see me as more than just <NpcName>Walter’s</> wife.//They see me as <NpcName>Bree</>.
Text.LocalizedString: People don’t do that here. They see me as more than just <NpcName>Walter’s</> wife.//They see me as <NpcName>Bree</>.

Text.SourceString: Too bad <NpcName>Sam</> isn’t selling pumpkins right now.//I’m craving pumpkin soup.
Text.LocalizedString: Too bad <NpcName>Sam</> isn’t selling pumpkins right now.//I’m craving pumpkin soup.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if <NpcName>Ben</> is around.//He might have some.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if <NpcName>Ben</> is around.//He might have some.

Text.SourceString: Too bad <NpcName>Sam</> isn’t selling blueberries right now.//I’m craving fresh blueberries. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Too bad <NpcName>Sam</> isn’t selling blueberries right now.//I’m craving fresh blueberries. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: I wonder if <NpcName>Ben</> is around.//He might have some.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if <NpcName>Ben</> is around.//He might have some.

Text.SourceString: The shampoo here smells divine. It’s just not the same when you wash your hair at home, even if you use the <Italic>exact</> same shampoo.
Text.LocalizedString: The shampoo here smells divine. It’s just not the same when you wash your hair at home, even if you use the <Italic>exact</> same shampoo.

Text.SourceString: It’s not that I don’t trust <NpcName>Luke</>.//<portrait=normal>I just want to know who he’s spending time with, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not that I don’t trust <NpcName>Luke</>.//<portrait=normal>I just want to know who he’s spending time with, you know?

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I’m asking too much. I mean, he’s my only son.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I’m asking too much. I mean, he’s my only son.

Text.SourceString: I was telling <NpcName>Dinda</> that <NpcName>Luke</> overthinks things sometimes. He’s always been like that.
Text.LocalizedString: I was telling <NpcName>Dinda</> that <NpcName>Luke</> overthinks things sometimes. He’s always been like that.

Text.SourceString: Poor thing. Can’t help himself.
Text.LocalizedString: Poor thing. Can’t help himself.

Text.SourceString: I can’t even begin to think about <NpcName>Luke</> getting married.//It makes me nervous.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t even begin to think about <NpcName>Luke</> getting married.//It makes me nervous.

Text.SourceString: I hope when he has his own family, he still has time to visit me and his dad.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope when he has his own family, he still has time to visit me and his dad.

Text.SourceString: I met <NpcName>Luke’s</> father when I was working.
Text.LocalizedString: I met <NpcName>Luke’s</> father when I was working.

Text.SourceString: Ha ha ha. Yes, love at first sight – something like that.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha ha. Yes, love at first sight – something like that.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Archie’s</> lovely. He says the funniest things.//<portrait=normal>I wonder if I’ll ever get grandkids from <NpcName>Luke</>.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Archie’s</> lovely. He says the funniest things.//<portrait=normal>I wonder if I’ll ever get grandkids from <NpcName>Luke</>.

Text.SourceString: It would be nice, yes. But I’m not a pushy person, so I won’t force him.//<portrait=annoyed>Though if he knows what’s good for him, he should start thinking about it.
Text.LocalizedString: It would be nice, yes. But I’m not a pushy person, so I won’t force him.//<portrait=annoyed>Though if he knows what’s good for him, he should start thinking about it.

Text.SourceString: Watch your step, <PlayerName>$player</>. <NPCName>Taco</> can sneak up on you.//<portrait=concerned>I’ve stepped on him getting up from my chair when he’d been asleep right there all along.
Text.LocalizedString: Watch your step, <PlayerName>$player</>. <NPCName>Taco</> can sneak up on you.//<portrait=concerned>I’ve stepped on him getting up from my chair when he’d been asleep right there all along.

Text.SourceString: Oh, don’t judge, dear.//I’m sure you’ve done the same thing with your pet.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, don’t judge, dear.//I’m sure you’ve done the same thing with your pet.

Text.SourceString: There was a point when <NPCName>Taco</> was very sick with a rare stomach bug.//<portrait=concerned>His vet in Pokyo put him on a strict diet. I was worried, of course.//My mind went to dark places.
Text.LocalizedString: There was a point when <NPCName>Taco</> was very sick with a rare stomach bug.//<portrait=concerned>His vet in Pokyo put him on a strict diet. I was worried, of course.//My mind went to dark places.

Text.SourceString: Thankfully, he recovered quickly.//He has a sensitive tummy.
Text.LocalizedString: Thankfully, he recovered quickly.//He has a sensitive tummy.

Text.SourceString: I simply don’t understand what <NpcName>Ben’s</> wearing.//A tank top in Summer, in the middle of the forest. Tsk, tsk, tsk.//Not a good call.
Text.LocalizedString: I simply don’t understand what <NpcName>Ben’s</> wearing.//A tank top in Summer, in the middle of the forest. Tsk, tsk, tsk.//Not a good call.

Text.SourceString: Everyone has a past, right, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>There’s no point in dwelling on what’s already happened.//<portrait=normal>It’s over. We’re new people today.
Text.LocalizedString: Everyone has a past, right, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>There’s no point in dwelling on what’s already happened.//<portrait=normal>It’s over. We’re new people today.

Text.SourceString: What matters is who we are now and who we will be tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: What matters is who we are now and who we will be tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: I ran into <NpcName>Charles</> yesterday, and he wasn’t wearing his lab coat.//<portrait=happy>He looked nice. I’m used to seeing him in the lab coat, but maybe change is good sometimes. Yeah.
Text.LocalizedString: I ran into <NpcName>Charles</> yesterday, and he wasn’t wearing his lab coat.//<portrait=happy>He looked nice. I’m used to seeing him in the lab coat, but maybe change is good sometimes. Yeah.

Text.SourceString: Are you looking forward to the Harvest Festival?//The display contest is always exciting to watch.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you looking forward to the Harvest Festival?//The display contest is always exciting to watch.

Text.SourceString: I secretly loathe going to dinner parties with <NpcName>Walter’s</> friends in the city.//I can just feel their scorn.
Text.LocalizedString: I secretly loathe going to dinner parties with <NpcName>Walter’s</> friends in the city.//I can just feel their scorn.

Text.SourceString: You make jam and stuff on your farm, don’t you? And you sell it?//<portrait=happy>Good for you.
Text.LocalizedString: You make jam and stuff on your farm, don’t you? And you sell it?//<portrait=happy>Good for you.

Text.SourceString: Wine lady? Hmm… Who called me that?
Text.LocalizedString: Wine lady? Hmm… Who called me that?

Text.SourceString: Oh. Dear <NpcName>Kira</> does like to tease. Maybe I should visit her charming little cabin again.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh. Dear <NpcName>Kira</> does like to tease. Maybe I should visit her charming little cabin again.

Text.SourceString: Things never make sense around here.//We’ll have perfectly happy customers, then suddenly they stop ordering.
Text.LocalizedString: Things never make sense around here.//We’ll have perfectly happy customers, then suddenly they stop ordering.

Text.SourceString: Does that happen to you too?//<portrait=annoyed>Oh, right. You just ship things overnight with <NpcName>Sam</>, huh? That makes it easy.//<portrait=normal>Maybe we’ll start using a third party like that.
Text.LocalizedString: Does that happen to you too?//<portrait=annoyed>Oh, right. You just ship things overnight with <NpcName>Sam</>, huh? That makes it easy.//<portrait=normal>Maybe we’ll start using a third party like that.

Text.SourceString: I get tense just thinking about distributing our wines.//Public relations and everything. Yada yada yada…
Text.LocalizedString: I get tense just thinking about distributing our wines.//Public relations and everything. Yada yada yada…

Text.SourceString: I don’t like dealing with stuff like that. I let <NpcName>Luke</> take care of it.//I’ve had enough wining and dining in my youth with <NpcName>Walter’s</> friends.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like dealing with stuff like that. I let <NpcName>Luke</> take care of it.//I’ve had enough wining and dining in my youth with <NpcName>Walter’s</> friends.

Text.SourceString: I moved here for a second chance. A new story. A new life.
Text.LocalizedString: I moved here for a second chance. A new story. A new life.

Text.SourceString: I still see my old friends sometimes. But now, we live so far away from our…er…old life.
Text.LocalizedString: I still see my old friends sometimes. But now, we live so far away from our…er…old life.

Text.SourceString: It’s really time for my hair treatment again, huh?//<portrait=annoyed>My hair feels so coarse. Blech!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s really time for my hair treatment again, huh?//<portrait=annoyed>My hair feels so coarse. Blech!

Text.SourceString: I’m just getting my hair blown out today, nothing fancy.//Something decent for a simple dinner tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m just getting my hair blown out today, nothing fancy.//Something decent for a simple dinner tonight.

Text.SourceString: The dinner is at home, of course.//<portrait=normal>I much prefer it that way.
Text.LocalizedString: The dinner is at home, of course.//<portrait=normal>I much prefer it that way.

Text.SourceString: New hairdo, <PlayerName>$player</>? It suits you.
Text.LocalizedString: New hairdo, <PlayerName>$player</>? It suits you.

Text.SourceString: My hair is a mess, but I’m simply too busy to go to the salon.//It’ll have to wait until later.
Text.LocalizedString: My hair is a mess, but I’m simply too busy to go to the salon.//It’ll have to wait until later.

Text.SourceString: Winter is the time to retouch my hair. A nice cut and color. The usual maintenance.//It’s when I have the <Italic>time</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is the time to retouch my hair. A nice cut and color. The usual maintenance.//It’s when I have the <Italic>time</>.

Text.SourceString: Winter is the time to retouch my hair. A nice cut and color. The usual maintenance.//It’s when I have the <Italic>time</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is the time to retouch my hair. A nice cut and color. The usual maintenance.//It’s when I have the <Italic>time</>.

Text.SourceString: Any other time of year, I’m simply too busy.
Text.LocalizedString: Any other time of year, I’m simply too busy.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think <NPCName>Taco</> likes the cats very much.//<portrait=normal>Oh, I’m not talking about just any cats. <NpcName>Erika’s</> cats. I’m sure you’ve seen them around.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think <NPCName>Taco</> likes the cats very much.//<portrait=normal>Oh, I’m not talking about just any cats. <NpcName>Erika’s</> cats. I’m sure you’ve seen them around.

Text.SourceString: He got hissed at by the brown one. Oh, that scared him, yeah!//<portrait=concerned>My poor baby.
Text.LocalizedString: He got hissed at by the brown one. Oh, that scared him, yeah!//<portrait=concerned>My poor baby.

Text.SourceString: If you like paintings, I recommend <NPCName>Dippa</>.//They produce one-of-a-kind art.
Text.LocalizedString: If you like paintings, I recommend <NPCName>Dippa</>.//They produce one-of-a-kind art.

Text.SourceString: For a price, of course. But we can’t put a price on art, can we, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: For a price, of course. But we can’t put a price on art, can we, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
